ter} zoospores to less than 10{\%} of the number settling on control surfaces. The antifouling {\textless}italic{\textgreater}alpP{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} gene was detected only in {\textless}named-content content-type="genus-species"{\textgreater}P. tunicata{\textless}/named-content{\textgreater} strains (with purple and yellow pigmentation), so other compounds/mechanisms must be present in the other {\textless}named-content content-type="genus-species"{\textgreater}Pseudoalteromonas{\textless}/named-content{\textgreater} strains with antifouling activity. {\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
