-type="genus-species"{\textgreater}Sphingobacteriales{\textless}/named-content{\textgreater} sequences. The overall effect of the WWTP inputs was that the two rivers, which were distinct in chemical and biological properties upstream of the WWTPs, were almost indistinguishable downstream. These results suggest that WWTP effluent has the potential to reduce the natural variability that exists among river ecosystems and indicate that WWTP effluent may contribute to biotic homogenization. {\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
